---
import Container from "../components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "../components/sectionhead.astro";
import CodeSandbox from "../components/CodeSandbox.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button";
import TextAndImage from "../components/TextAndImage.astro";
import List from "../components/List";
import Celebration from "../components/Celebration";
import Excalidraw from "../components/Excalidraw.astro";
import WavingHand from "../components/WavingHand.astro";
import PDF from "../components/PDF.astro";
---

<Container>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <h2 class="text-6xl my-20 leading-normal">
            <WavingHand />Welcome to your coding journey!
        </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <TextAndImage
            title="First up, Github"
            content="You're making a great decision by choosing to learn how to code. As part of your course, you'll need to set up a GitHub account. Why, you ask? Well, GitHub is an essential tool used by millions of developers around the globe. It's where you'll store your code projects, collaborate with other learners, and even contribute to open-source projects later on."
            imageURL="/day1/github-pages.jpg"
        />
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-5">
            Here's a simple, step-by-step guide to help you sign up for GitHub:
        </h3>

        <List
            items={[
                "Start the sign-up process: Click on the green 'Sign up' button located at the top-right corner of the page.",
                "Enter your details: You'll be directed to a new page. Here, you need to fill in your preferred username, email address, and a secure password.",
                "Enter your details: You'll be directed to a new page. Here, you need to fill in your preferred username, email address, and a secure password. 'Complete the security check: To confirm that you're not a robot, you'll be asked to complete a short task.",
                "Click that you have understood and are ready to go to github!",
            ]}
        />
        <Button href="https://github.com/join" />
        <!-- You can continue the list here -->
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
            Here's a YouTube video to help you if you are a visual learner!
        </h3>
        <div
            class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-400 via-red-500 to-yellow-500 text-white rounded-xl shadow-md my-5 w-auto inline-block"
        >
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
                <iframe
                    width="560"
                    height="315"
                    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QUtk-Uuq9nE"
                    title="YouTube video player"
                    frameborder="0"
                    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                    allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </p>
        </div>
        <Button href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QUtk-Uuq9nE" />
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <TextAndImage
            title="Secondly, signing up for CodeSandbox with your GitHub Account"
            content="CodeSandbox is an online code editor where you can create and share projects directly from your browser. It's especially great for web development, and supports a variety of different languages and frameworks. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to sign up for CodeSandbox using your new GitHub account:"
            imageURL="/day1/og.jpg"
        />

        <List
            items={[
                "Visit the CodeSandbox website: Open your browser and start the sign-up process.",
                "Click on the 'Sign In' button located at the top-right corner of the page.",
                "Choose GitHub as your sign-in method: You'll see different options for signing in. Click on the 'Continue with GitHub' button.",
                "Authorize CodeSandbox: If you're already logged into GitHub, you'll be asked to authorize CodeSandbox to access your GitHub account. Click 'Authorize CodeSandbox' to proceed. If you're not logged in, you'll be prompted to log into GitHub first.",
            ]}
        />

        <Button href="https://codesandbox.io/signin" />
        <!-- You can continue the list here -->
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <TextAndImage
            title="Complete the Day 1 Workshop sheet"
            content="This concise worksheet provides a systematic approach to website development. It starts by identifying the project's purpose and setting precise goals. Next, it helps outline your target audience, defining who would benefit from your website. The focus then shifts to the website's design, integrating wireframes and your unique branding elements. Finally, it offers a practical guide for managing weekly tasks, ensuring efficient progress towards your website development goals."
            imageURL="/day1/design.webp"
        />
        <List
            items={[
                "Grab the printout worksheet and begin filling in the right-hand side with all your creative ideas.",
                "Once you're finished, make sure to keep the worksheet in a safe place.",
                "Remember, you'll need to refer back to these ideas tomorrow, so ensure it's easily accessible!",
            ]}
        />
    </div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 mt-20">
        Use Excalidraw below when prompted by the lecturer.
    </h3>
    <Excalidraw />
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8 text-gray-700">
        <TextAndImage
            title="And lastly, cloning the CodeF starter template "
            content="We're excited to introduce our development template that combines Astro and Tailwind CSS. Astro's innovative approach minimizes JavaScript, delivering swift, efficient websites. Tailwind CSS complements this by providing a utility-first framework for creating visually compelling, custom UIs with ease. This fusion simplifies your workflow, resulting in an enhanced performance and user experience. It's the perfect starting point for your web projects, let's push the boundaries of web development together!"
            imageURL="/day1/astro.webp"
        />
        <List
            items={[
                "Navigate to the CodeSandbox window below these steps.",
                "Click the green expand button to enter the development area.",
                "Click on the 'Fork' button located in the upper right corner of the sandbox environment.",
                "CodeSandbox will then create a new copy (fork) of the sandbox in your account.",
                "Rename the new sandbox if you want, by clicking on the title.",
                "Start making your changes in the newly forked sandbox.",
            ]}
        />
    </div>
    <CodeSandbox basic sandbox="hopeful-sea-249w2x" />
    <Celebration client:only />
</Container>
